News24 Correspondent(File, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Polokwane - A four-year-old girl and a woman, aged 25, burnt to death following a horrific collision over the weekend on the N1 just outside Makhado, Limpopo police said."It is alleged that two motor vehicles, which were going [in] opposite directions, have collided head-on," Lt. Col. Moatshe Ngoepe said in a statement about the crash which occurred on Saturday night.The toddler and women who died were travelling together in a Corsa Bakkie. &nbsp;The other vehicle &ndash; A four-wheel drive SUV &ndash; also caught fire. The driver, a 34-year-old man, survived with serious burns and is recovering in hospital. &nbsp;Police have opened a case of culpable homicide. The cause of the accident is not yet known. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.